<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="464" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,150,1004]" pageId="35" pageNumber="464">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,186,212]" pageId="35" pageNumber="464">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a combination of two Greek terms, 
<emphasis box="[978,1029,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="464">titan</emphasis>
(gigantic) and 
<emphasis box="[1196,1257,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="464">chela</emphasis>
(claw), in reference to the very large claw-like inner and outer prongs of the male gonostylus.
